title: For Sale/Trade:  Operation Shield Our Troops- Please help.
postcontent:
Good afternoon,

My fiancée is a Mary Kay representative, and she is spear-heading a fund raiser to send our troops who are stationed in the Middle East sunscreen & lip balm sets.  Operation Shield Our Troops is a small way of saying thank you to our military serving in the harsh desert climates of the Middle East.  Will this totally nullify the sacrifice being made by them for all of us, in short, no, but if it can alleviate one aspect of the many conditions they deal with everyday, then what would it be to give that gift to them.  Just to let them know that they are being thought of, appreciated, and possibly reinforce their mettle in the endeavor they have chosen to do, is a small price on our part to help them in any way we can. So please give generously, and know that for your donation you have made one of our troops time in service that much better.  Every set that is donated, there will be a personalized card saying from whom the gift was donated by, so they know exactly who supported them in their time of sacrifice. If you could please circulate this, it would be greatly appreciated. She has set up a donation page; here is the link to the page, thank you.

 http://www.gofundme.com/shieldourtroops   

Best wishes,
Charles L. MacLennan

title: For Sale:  PSA on Scam posts and listings
postcontent:
I've noticed in the past few months an increasing number of scam posts of some guns way under retail value. This is a reminder that if a deal is too good to be true it probably is.

Many of these posts just in this region are listed under Wisconsin, Wisconsin with no general area given. So when you go to contact this person and ask where the gun will be coming from they say Arizona, and when you use another email address to ask them if they will sell locally you get no response.

So listings like this: http://www.armslist.com/posts/4283083/wisconsin-rifles-for-sale--fn-scar-16-16--5-56-223-nib-

should come up as a red flag, especially with the way that everything is worded. Please do not reply to an email address other than the reply button provided on the classified, do not send these people money through money order, but please do flag these posts as you see them.

Others: http://www.armslist.com/posts/4283253/milwaukee-wisconsin-rifles-for-sale--fnh-scar-16s-nib-5-56-x-45mm-

title: For Sale:  Nice Squires-Bingham AR-15 Style Black Wood 22 Semi Rifle + Sling
postcontent: There are loads of 22 versions of the AR-15 out there and probably $40 to $60 more gets you a tactical version with moving stock and rails. This is not for the guy or girl who wants that. I collected 22 rifles (79 of them) and like the harder to find but good looking ones. This is the reliable and common Armscor M20 inside, and they added black painted wood stock, a 3-prong flash hider, a carry handle with sight that attaches to the scope rail, and the most realistic magazine of all. A fully metal body mag that has the standard 10 or 15 round M20 mag mounted in it permanently. The gun shoots Hi-Vel 22 great and accurately. I can make a 12 gauge empty dance down the 25 yard range. A great beginner rifle for a kid as they get a cool looking gun that is semi-auto and accurate. The bluing is deep and dark and flawless on all blued metal parts and the wood is overall excellent with various small scuffs and dings but none through the paint. 15 round mags are all over Gunbroker. This has the original leather sling it had on it when I got it, and comes with 1 mag. I am pretty sure it is 10 rounds. I can sell private to FL residents with a valid CWP (if no permit, we can talk) and will ship to FFL for $28 Full set of good photos available on request

title: For Sale/Trade:  Turkish 38/46 "Short Rifle"
postcontent:
This is not a common Turkish Mauser, but rather a rare "Short Rifle".  Chambered in 8mm Mauser and based on the German Kar 98AZ, only an estimated 15,000 were made between 1944 and 1946 at the K.Kale factory.  Rumor has it that they were issued exclusively to Turkish Marines.  It also includes the hard to find sling, cleaning rod, bayonet and scabbard.

The bore is worn but there's no corrosion - I'd rate it about a 7 out of 10. There are no cracks or gouges in the wood, and as with nearly all Turk rifles, the serial numbers don't match. I've checked the headspace and the bolt will not close on a FIELD gauge. 

This is a $400 value, but my price is $300 cash face-to-face in Jacksonville, FL.  I'll provide a Bill of Sale for the buyer and will require a signed copy for my records.  

I'll also entertain trade offers for 9mm handguns, and throw in some 8mm ammo for the right trade.

title: For Sale:  Chinese MAK 90 in Pristine Condition - with 2175 Rounds of Ammo
postcontent:
A hard to find Chinese MAK 90 with matching numbers. This rifle was imported by C.J.A. SFLD, MN. It is in pristine condition and is considered one of the best and most sought after AK's. You'll be hard pressed to find a nicer one. It has a 1.5mm thick receiver vs. 1.0mm receiver on most stamped AK rifles and comes with a chrome lined barrel. Unlike your standard MAK 90's, this one comes with a spring loaded firing pin, a much more pronounced feed ramp and a heavy duty recoil assembly with a thick steel rod vs two slim wire rods that are interconnected at the middle of the assembly. I've been told that with the spring loaded firing pin etc, that it "probably" started as a Poly Tech but was "neutered" when it reached the US, but I can't confirm that so I am selling it as an exceptionally nice Chinese Mak 90. It will also include the original sling, (1) 30 round metal magazine and (1) 40 round metal magazine. 

You won't be disappointed! 

Email me for additional pictures.
